Amazon RME tech perks

system

2025-07-27T00:30:06.548217Z user

So does every rme tech hired at Amazon get an Uber business account and Lyft Business and air BNB for work account?

2025-07-27T00:30:06.744587Z assistant

2025-07-27T00:30:07.577142Z tool

2025-07-27T00:30:08.853252Z assistant

It appears that no, Amazon does not automatically issue Uber for Business, Lyft Business, or Airbnb for Work accounts to RME (Reliability & Maintenance Engineering) techs or any regular Amazon employees by default.

Heres whats relevant:

Amazon Maintenance Technicians (RME techs)

  • Maintenance technicians at Amazon are typically fulltime employees (not contractors) and receive standard employee benefits like health/dental/vision insurance, 401(k), paid family leave, and access to Amazon Extras for employee discounts on services, travel and more citeturn0search7turn0search1.
  • However, rideshare or lodging services (Uber Business, Lyft Business, Airbnb for Work) are not standard automatic perks offered to this group.

Uber & Lyft Business Accounts

  • Uber and Lyft offer separate business account solutions for companiesbut these are optional and must be set up by the employer through admin onboarding. Employees are invited individuallytheres no blanket enrollment citeturn0search18turn0search4.
  • Individual fulfillment center staff have reported that some sites may offer rideshare discounts or reimbursement programs, but availability varies by facility and must be confirmed locallytypically via HR citeturn0search14.

Airbnb for Work

  • Airbnb for Work is also a separate corporate travel platform and is not included automatically in Amazon employee benefits.
  • Amazons internal travel policies for field or remote technicians may use standard booking systems. Theres no public evidence that Airbnb for Work is automatically enabled.

Benefit Summary

Benefit RME Tech / Maintenance Employee Remarks
Health, dental, vision, 401(k), leave Standard benefit for full-time employees
Amazon Extras discounts Includes travel, insurance, cellplans etc
Uber for Business account (not by default) Requires company adoption and individual invite
Lyft Business account (not automatic) Similar to Ubermust be set up
Airbnb for Work account (not standard) Not part of employee benefit menu

So what can you do?

If youre interested in Uber Business, Lyft Business, or Airbnb for Work access:

  1. Check with your HR or manager to see if your location/facility has an expense or rideshare program.
  2. Ask whether there is an option to be invited to a corporate Uber/Lyft business profile.
  3. If you travel regularly, inquire about approved booking tools, and whether Airbnb travel is permitted or reimbursable.

TL;DR

Amazon does not automatically issue Uber, Lyft, or Airbnb business profiles to RME techs or maintenance field techs. You can access regular employee perks and discounts, but rideshare and lodging business accounts require opt-in and setup by your company or facility.

Let me know if you'd like guidance on how to ask HR about ride-share or travel benefits!
